params.description: Immutable. The relative resource name of the metastore service, of the form: projects/{project_number}/locations/{location_id}/services/{service_id}.

params.description: Output only. The time when the metastore service was created.

params.description: User-defined labels for the metastore service.

params.description: Output only. The URI of the endpoint used to access the metastore service.

params.description: The TCP port at which the metastore service is reached. Default: 9083.

params.name: data.state
params.description: Output only. The current state of the metastore service.

params.description: Output only. Additional information about the current state of the metastore service, if available.

params.description: Output only. A Cloud Storage URI (starting with gs://) that specifies where artifacts related to the metastore service are stored.

params.name: data.tier
params.description: The tier of the service.

params.name: data.metadata_integration
params.description: The setting that defines how metastore metadata should be integrated with external services and systems.

params.name: data.maintenance_window
params.description: The one hour maintenance window of the metastore service. This specifies when the service can be restarted for maintenance purposes in UTC time.

params.name: data.uid
params.description: Output only. The globally unique resource identifier of the metastore service.

params.name: data.metadata_management_activity
params.description: Output only. The metadata management activities of the metastore service.

params.name: data.release_channel
params.description: Immutable. The release channel of the service. If unspecified, defaults to STABLE.
